                                                <h2 class="all-caps">Required Compliance</h2>
                                                <p>The question in the minds of many readers is “what is required for compliance?” Furthermore, “What is optional and what is obligatory as it relates to the different zones?” Without the iconic branding images of logos and brand color palettes, the ability to create a consistent and exceptional Brand experience in a hotel lobby is more of a nuanced art. Therefore we rely on providing consistent architectural brand cues. The <a href="#" class="inline-link all-caps">Brand Narrative</a> clearly outlines the vision to the experience, personality, and architectural pillars of Hilton hotels.</p>


                                                <h2>How to Maintain the Hilton Brand</h2>
                                                <p><a href="#" class="inline-link all-caps">Design Drivers</a> &amp; <a href="#" class="inline-link all-caps">The Guest Journey</a> Chapters 3 &amp; 4: The quality of style and activity appropriate for the Hilton Brand is described in this chapter and depends on the context of each hotel.</p>

                                                <p><a href="#" class="inline-link all-caps">Defined Zones</a> Chapter 5: Each Hilton Lobby must have a logical flow of space, distinct design details and possess the primary zones outlined in this design narrative.</p>
